Serpentine Falls National Park just outside the town of Serpentine which about 35 minutes drive East of Mandurah. 
The Serpentine Falls National Park is open from 8.30am to 5pm daily with an entry fee of $9 per car (though if you park your car by the picnic grounds, you will avoid this fee.)

value: has well kept picnic grounds set in natural surroundings. The falls are located about 400 mts from the picnic grounds but there is a falls car park closer, The falls descend into a deep, clear pool of water which is perfect for swimming. Concrete has been used to make steps that ascend into the water making it easier for those with disabilities. During the weekends, public and school holidays, the falls are usually crowded. Visiting outside of these periods would be a more enjoyable visit.

There are several camp sites surrounding the falls, For further information phone (08) 9525-2128
